28/09/2005
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- Software giant Microsoft has picked Belgrade as one of its five global development centres, the company announced Tuesday (27 September). 
The facility will focus on developing technology for tablet personal computers. 
Deputy Prime Minister Miroljub Labus said the decision demonstrates the political situation in Serbia has improved and sends a positive signal to other foreign investors. 
(AFP - 27/09/05)
